## Classify `metric_type`

Before either detection command fires queries, classify the metric into one
of: `count`, `unique_count`, `ratio`, `funnel`, `retention`, `unknown`.
Both `metric-anomaly` and `metric-drift` reference this single table — do
not duplicate it into the command files.

| Detected | Classification |
|---|---|
| Report type `funnels` | `funnel` |
| Report type `retention` | `retention` |
| Query template has A/B form or `% of total` (conversion rate, session rate, etc.) | `ratio` |
| Single-series count (event count, event count distinct users) | `count` |
| Single-series unique count | `unique_count` |
| Formula metric / custom SQL / anything else | `unknown` |

Store as `metric_type` on the metric series object. Used in every verdict
card and in special-case routing (funnel, retention).

